i386/tcg: add Cyrix MediaGX 0F 3C compatibility shim (Pinball 2000).

Per the Cyrix MediaGX databook, opcode 0F 3C is CPU_WRITE (EBX = internal
CPU-register address, EAX = data; the value is written into a CPU-internal
configuration register such as the BLT buffer base/pointer or GP-DMA
descriptor). True CPU_WRITE / CPU_READ (0F 3D) / BB0_RESET (0F 3A) /
BB1_RESET (0F 3B) semantics are NOT implemented here.

Instead, this patch reproduces the observable side effect of the legacy
Unicorn / low-RAM IDT[6] stub that the Pinball 2000 XINU bring-up code
already relied on:

    [DS:EDX]   := EAX        ; 32-bit
    [DS:EDX+4] := EBX        ; 32-bit
    EDX        += 8

Reference: unicorn.old/src/cpu.c:587-628 and the deleted host-side stub
qemu/p2k-cyrix-0f3c.c. The XINU users of 0F 3C only rely on this
pointer-walk pattern, not on the real internal-register address space, so
the shim is sufficient for the four-config matrix.

Without this patch, vanilla QEMU TCG raises #UD (vector 6) on 0F 3C and
the bare XINU IDT lands in trap_dispatch() ("Trap to monitor"). With it,
the entire qemu/p2k-cyrix-0f3c.c module (RAM stub at 0x540 + IDT[6]
patch) becomes unnecessary and is deleted.

Long-term direction: implement real MediaGX CPU_WRITE / CPU_READ /
BB?_RESET semantics, ideally gated to the pinball2000 / MediaGX machine
so other i386 guests retain their #UD behaviour. For now this shim is
clearly named (gen_CYRIX_0F3C_shim) and clearly documented as
compatibility only.

--- a/target/i386/tcg/emit.c.inc
+++ b/target/i386/tcg/emit.c.inc
@@ -4648,6 +4648,42 @@
 #define gen_WRMSR gen_unreachable
 #endif
 
+/* pinball2000: Cyrix MediaGX/5530 opcode 0F 3C compatibility shim.
+ *
+ * The Cyrix MediaGX databook documents 0F 3C as CPU_WRITE: EBX holds an
+ * internal-CPU-register address, EAX holds the data, and the result is
+ * written into a CPU-internal configuration register (BLT buffer base /
+ * pointer, GP-DMA descriptors, etc). True CPU_WRITE semantics are NOT
+ * implemented here.
+ *
+ * Instead, this generator reproduces the observable side effect of the
+ * Unicorn / legacy QEMU low-RAM IDT[6] stub that the Pinball 2000 XINU
+ * bring-up code is known to rely on:
+ *
+ *     [DS:EDX]   := EAX        ; 32-bit
+ *     [DS:EDX+4] := EBX        ; 32-bit
+ *     EDX        += 8
+ *
+ * (See unicorn.old/src/cpu.c:587-628 and the deleted
+ * qemu/p2k-cyrix-0f3c.c host-side stub.) The XINU users of 0F 3C
+ * happen to only care about this pointer-walk pattern, not about the
+ * real CPU_WRITE register address space, so emulating the shim is
+ * sufficient for the matrix.
+ *
+ * EIP is advanced past the 2-byte opcode by the caller after this
+ * generator returns. Long-term direction is real CPU_WRITE / CPU_READ
+ * (0F 3D) handling, gated to the MediaGX/pinball2000 machine; for now
+ * this shim replaces the dirtier IDT-patch + low-RAM-stub layer.
+ */
+static void gen_CYRIX_0F3C_shim(DisasContext *s, X86DecodedInsn *decode)
+{
+    gen_lea_v_seg(s, cpu_regs[R_EDX], R_DS, s->override);
+    tcg_gen_qemu_st_tl(cpu_regs[R_EAX], s->A0, s->mem_index, MO_LEUL);
+    tcg_gen_addi_tl(s->A0, s->A0, 4);
+    tcg_gen_qemu_st_tl(cpu_regs[R_EBX], s->A0, s->mem_index, MO_LEUL);
+    tcg_gen_addi_tl(cpu_regs[R_EDX], cpu_regs[R_EDX], 8);
+}
+
 static void gen_WRxxBASE(DisasContext *s, X86DecodedInsn *decode)
 {
     TCGv base = cpu_seg_base[s->modrm & 8 ? R_GS : R_FS];
--- a/target/i386/tcg/decode-new.c.inc
+++ b/target/i386/tcg/decode-new.c.inc
@@ -1178,6 +1178,13 @@
     [0x34] = X86_OP_ENTRY0(SYSENTER,                          chk2(i64_amd, prot_or_vm86)),
     [0x35] = X86_OP_ENTRY0(SYSEXIT,                           chk3(i64_amd, prot, cpl0)),
 
+    /* pinball2000: Cyrix MediaGX 0F 3C compatibility shim (NOT true
+     * CPU_WRITE). Stores EAX into [DS:EDX], EBX into [DS:EDX+4], then
+     * EDX += 8. Reproduces the observable side effect of the legacy
+     * Unicorn IDT[6] stub. Generator in emit.c.inc. Real MediaGX
+     * CPU_WRITE/CPU_READ semantics are not implemented. */
+    [0x3C] = X86_OP_ENTRY0(CYRIX_0F3C_shim),
+
